# REST API conventions

When creating or modifying API endpoints:

- Use appropriate HTTP methods (GET for reads, POST for creates, PUT/PATCH for updates, DELETE for deletes).
- Return proper status codes: 200 OK, 201 Created, 400 Bad Request, 404 Not Found, 500 Server Error.
- Use consistent URL patterns (`/api/v1/resource`, `/api/v1/resource/:id`).
- Include error handling with clear, actionable error messages.
